  "prompt": "Why can't I answer a question twice on Quora?",
  "response": "On Quora, each question is designed to have a single, unique answer from each user in order to maintain the platform's structure and promote diverse perspectives. This encourages users to express their thoughts in one comprehensive answer rather than multiple responses that might convey similar points. If you wish to provide additional insights or updates to your answer, you can edit your original response instead. If you feel like you have a completely different perspective, you can do so by creating a new answer under the same question, as long as it hasn\u2019t been submitted by you already.",
